narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Again, the course was sort of a hodgepodge of feelings and film and whatever else, but I found it a relief from the typical Yale course. If you loved the films you'd love talking about them. If you need to be entertained, look elsewhere.

This is a great class if you have any interest in experimental cinema, because it exposes you to a lot of material that you wouldn't necessarily come across otherwise (some are only on 16mm film). Professor Francis is very knowledgeable and also chill--there are weekly screenings and reading responses but we only had to do two 5-page papers. I learned so much and it was a fun experience, I highly recommend it!
Great opportunity to look at films that you would otherwise never have access too. I would definitely recommend to another student.

It's probably good to get an overview of experimental film and filmmakers in order to have a more well-rounded knowledge of film in general. But be warned, many of these films are pretty painful to sit through.
This is a good 5th class but I wouldnt suggest it as something too serious
